race.comment: KEEP IT REAL (6) looks well placed. He's finished second in all three starts to date, resuming at Sale with a solid run, working home well late after drawing wide. He gets every chance from barrier three this time in what looks a winnable maiden for a horse with his upside. BRUTAL COMMAND (3) is a gelding by Brutal on debut for the Hayes yard. He won a jumpout at Flemington and trialled well officially at Bendigo. He should take beating. INCONTESTABLE (5) ran a good race on debut at Werribee when working home well for second. He should improve for that and has claims. SHE'S LOADED (10) ran well fresh at Stawell, clearly her best career effort to date. She can go on with it now. ZOUSOUTH (9) was close up fresh and should take catching.
